pes.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.codehaus.btm:btm:2.1.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Ehcache's DefaultTransactionManagerLookup supports discovering Bitronix; exercising that normal transaction-manager integration requires a concrete JTA implementation.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.geronimo.specs:geronimo-jms_1.1_spec:1.1.1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Bitronix declares the JMS API optional but its resource classes reference javax.jms; include it to keep transaction-manager coverage classpath-complete under JVM and native-image analysis.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Keep tests hermetic by disabling Ehcache update checks, e.g. set the system property net.sf.ehcache.skipUpdateCheck=true or use Configuration.updateCheck(false). If exercising Bitronix discovery, write a temporary bitronix.properties file, set bitronix.tm.configuration to it, use journal=null and disableJmx=true, and clear the property/shut down Bitronix after the test.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The reported 2.5.0 failure is a missing reflection registration for net.sf.ehcache.store.DefaultElementValueComparator, so setup alone will not fix the native-image run.\",\n    \"Simple in-memory cache coverage does not need the transaction dependencies; they are justified only if preserving or improving transaction/DefaultTransactionManagerLookup coverage.\",\n    \"Avoid Terracotta clustered-cache paths unless intentionally tested, because they would introduce external server concerns not needed for core Ehcache coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_00061505ee61f8f8016a42fae09904819496a4eb9fc9a3de30\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1284, "output": 1315, "cacheRead": 44032, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 46631